# Cohort-2 secrecy contract for T3 (Workflow Orchestration).
#
# We DO ship ``public_eval_50_mock_responses.json`` — it is required for
# ``make eval-orchestrate`` to function locally and is harmless against
# the hidden eval, which uses a disjoint set of 500 task IDs that are
# rotated per submission (see WS1.3 in the platform repo). A candidate
# who hardcodes from the public mocks earns a perfect score on the
# 50 public task IDs (which appear on no leaderboard) and 0 % on the
# hidden 500 (which is what counts).
#
# What we do NOT ship is the hidden mock responses. Block any file that
# could expose them by accident.
hidden_*_mock_responses.json
hidden_eval_*.json
